tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All blood counts are within or near normal limits except for a slightly decreased hematocrit and mildly elevated platelet mean volume and distribution width. These findings may indicate mild hemoconcentration or early changes in platelet production or activation, but there is no evidence of significant anemia, infection, or thrombocytopenia. Clinical correlation is recommended.
